I have a similar problem, the biome maps don't appear. Am also on Mac OS X.

I'll try to get a debugging version to you guys tomorrow evening. Probably a directory issue.

For those of you with having problems with Custom Biomes, please try this version. It isn't any different, but produces a much more verbose log file. Please download, run, and report the results from your ksp.log. Thanks!

Hey Trueborn! I *love* your work, and would *love* to have CustomBiomes packaged for the Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (CKAN). I don't suppose you'd also consider putting your releases up on KerbalStuff by any chance? We have a bot that works well with the KerbalStuff API, which means that CKAN users will be able to install or upgrade new mods from KerbalStuff almost as soon as they go on-line.

Many, many thanks!

~ Paul

So for my reference, what is the path you used to have it installed in? /Applications/KSP_osx/GameData/CustomBiomes/...?

Yes, that's right. Mods are typically in KSP_osx/GameData/, though the KSP_osx folder can be safely renamed and moved anywhere.

KSP.app is an executable folder with the actual binary buried inside along with the Mono runtime, planet textures, etc.
